{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02006/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02006"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:20:06"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A framed photo of a bride in a dark room."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02006","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02006"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1/8f14b78b-b2f2-43f0-9e99-b97f794d6cd0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:25:36.769Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The photograph of Reynolds’s mother is shot in a close-up, stressing its significance as Reynolds’s hand reaches out and grips the frame from the left. It is lit up when Reynolds turns on the lamp (off screen). This knowledge that Reynolds shares with Alma illuminates their relationship. The ghostly <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW26979212 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-12919.html\"><u>vision</u></a> of his mother that Reynolds will have after Alma poisons him for the first time matches this photograph, thus underscoring how he idolizes this particular version of his mother—young, in a wedding gown, fixed rather than dynamic.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:665.2533039647577,64.4933920704845,822.114537444934,993.1607929515417"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1/307f2adf-d09c-4651-a648-788701bea42c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T15:25:46.150Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In a Q&amp;A at the Palm Springs International Film Festival, PTA notes that Reynolds’s bringing up his mother on his first date with Alma should be a “red flag” but also that many of the dressmakers he researched for the film had domineering mothers who greatly influenced their lives (Shackleton, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW45894097 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=au7NMfNWrhE\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD Q&amp;A</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02006/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:34.48237885462554,63.975770925110105,242.0814977973568,147.86343612334792"}}}]}]}]}